- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with spectral analysis of networks and graph partitioning, which are common topics in social and information networks research.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a new algorithm for graph partitioning.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as spectral clustering is a popular machine learning technique for graph partitioning.
- cs.SD (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses matrix perturbation theory to derive theoretical approximations of spectral projections.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper involves theoretical analysis of matrix perturbations and spectral projections.
